Plutarch Life of Lysander: According to Duris, he was the first Greek to whom the cities built altars and made sacrifice as to a God, and the first to whom were sung pacans, one of which they relate to have begun as follows:

We will sing the general of holy Greece who comes from the spacious town of Sparta, O Paean O !

Moreover the Samians decreed that their festival of Hera should be called the Lysandreia.
